detaileddescription.para:
Read-only property provides access to specifying the Axis grid. E.g. grid.axis:"XY"
AxisGrid

The x-axis AxisSpec object for this Axis. This provides access to the axis label, the major and minor ticks, etc.
AxisSpec

The y-axis AxisSpec object for this Axis. This provides access to the axis label, the major and minor ticks, etc.
AxisSpec

Sets all the data limits of the Axis at once.
minX, maxX, minY, maxY

Set the minimim X data limit.
AxisBase::limits

Set the maximum X data limit.
Axis2DBase::limits

Set the minimim Y data limit.
Axis2DBase::limits

Set the maximum Y data limit.
Axis2DBase::limits
If aspectRatio is larger than 0, the axis will enforce this ratio at all times. Note: aspectRatio = x/y

If true, the automatic axis limits will fit the plots in the axis as tightly as possible. If false, the axis will round the y-axis up to whole numbers (dependent on the scale of the axis). E.g. 894 -> 900, 8894 -> 9000
The handle property provides Nutmeg a way of identifying this Axis. By default, this is "axis".
A rectangle that defines the actual plotting area in this axis.
Set the title of this axis.
Font Define the Font to be used for the title. Can be used as a group property: titleFont{bold:true,family:"Arial",pointSize:16}
See QML's documentation for details on its basic Font type.
The color of the title text.
